      "raw_text": "(By United Press Leased Wire)\n\n\nWENATCHEE, May 27.-The\nGreat Northern railway this\nmorning began the use OF teIe-\nphones for train dispatchine\nbetween the sound and Spo-\nkane, marking the beginning\nOF the end of the telegrapher\non Hill roads. The phones cut\nIn this morning are those be-\ntween Spokane and Lesven-\nworth. The phone system be-\ntween Spokane and Troy,\nMont, will be ready inside of\nq week. When these are In\nuse, the Great Northern will\nhave about 2200 miles Of track\nover which the telephone has\nreplaced the telegraph."
